import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    scores = np.zeros_like(bins, dtype=np.float64)
    
    # Calculate scores based on the inverse ratio of bin index
    scores = 1.0 / (np.arange(len(bins)) + 1)
    
    # Raise the remaining capacity of each bin to the power of three
    scores *= np.power(bins, 3)
    
    # Disable bins with maximum capacity
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    scores[bins == max_capacity] = 0.0
    
    return scores
